            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p>Friend, you see here laid out the tomb  of Nassiane, a revered Christian, gentle of mood, loving of her husband, who competed with Penelope in virtue. Here lies Nassiane, having lived (in God?) well and blamelessly for 32 years, 10 months.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>The text was essentially established by Ferrua, who disposed of the speculative restorations of Strazzulla and clarified the various orthographic variations.</p>
            </div>
